pre-update-checks:

This is a script customers can execute before starting an update to check if
all (most) requirements for the update are fulfilled.

These checks include all "read-only" checks from the preup.
In the future we should move all "read-only" checks from the preup to the
pre-update-checks-* script and make the updater execute this test script so
that we do not need to maintain both versions.

At the moment the release (by univention) and execution (by customers) of the
check script is a complete manual process.

Release:
 * copy script to ftp/download/univention-update-checks
   -> scp checks/pre-update-checks-4.4 omar:@/var/univention/buildsystem2/mirror/ftp/download/univention-update-checks/pre-update-checks-4.4.new
 * check changes
 * sign the file
 * update the mirror

Execution:
-> curl -OOs http://univention-repository.knut.univention.de/download/univention-update-checks/pre-update-checks-4.4{,.gpg}
OR
-> curl -OOs https://updates.software-univention.de/download/univention-update-checks/pre-update-checks-4.4{,.gpg}
-> gpgv --keyring /usr/share/keyrings/univention-archive-key-ucs-4x.gpg pre-update-checks-4.4.gpg pre-update-checks-4.4 && bash pre-update-checks-4.4
